<HEADLINE>
LAYNE CHRISTENSEN ACQUIRES TWO LOUISIANA OIL AND GAS SERVICE
COMPANIES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RANDOLPH HEASTER  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Layne Christensen Co. on Tuesday announced the acquisition of
two Louisiana-based oil and gas service companies.
</P>
<P>
   Layne, based in Mission Woods, Kan., purchased the assets of
Vibration Technologies LLC and Toledo Oil &AMP; Gas Services Inc. Terms
of the deals were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Vibration Technologies is based in Shreveport and Toledo Oil in
Broussard. Both are technological specialists in the oil and gas
industry.
</P>
<P>
   ``We feel both of these companies are on the leading technical
edge in their respective specialties and are well positioned for
growth as oil and gas markets begin to recover,'' said Andrew B.
Schmitt, Layne's president and chief executive officer.
</P>
</TEXT>
