<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN - DAYTON, Ohio - Mary Brookins' work with Planned
Parenthood finally comes to an end after 31 years as an advocate
for family planning and ``contraceptive equity.'' (McCarty, Dayton
Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN - It was never a conscious decision, but over
the past several years I kept turning down the volume on my car
radio. Finally, I quit turning the darn thing on. I now prefer my
own thoughts to the distractions of a car radio, tape deck or CD
player. It's strange how things turn out. (Nethaway, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN - AUSTIN, Texas - If you're new to Austin, you
should know that this city has its own unique time zone. It's
pretty simple. Austin Standard Time or Austin Daylight Saving Time
both run about 15 or 20 minutes off from Central Standard or
Central Daylight Time. Being a punctual person, the unofficial
Austin time zone is annoying to me. But it's like the heat. It's a
part of living here that you have to accept or go crazy. (Kelso,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   JEFFERSON-COLUMN - This column will not move today. (Jefferson,
Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
