<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990707.0084 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 11:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1632 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NEWS-QUESTIONS08-COX     07-07 1524
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NEWS-QUESTIONS08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Q &AMP; A ON THE NEWS
 &HT;    By Colin Bessonette
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Have a question about the news? Colin Bessonette will try to get
an answer. Call 404-222-2002, or write him at The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, Ga. 30302, or e-mail
him at q&AMP;(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Q: Can you tell me how to get in touch with former Sen. Bill
Bradley's presidential campaign?
</P>
<P>
   A: The Democrat's official website _ www.billbradley.com _
offers many options for campaign contributions, plus information on
Bradley and some of his speeches. To get in touch with the campaign
the old-fashioned way, write Bill Bradley for President, Inc., 396
Pleasant Valley Way, West Orange, N.J. 07052. Or call the campaign
headquarters toll-free at 1-888-643-9799.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have a Government Approval form to have the air bag on-off
switch installed in my Ford. I have yet to find a Ford dealership
that will install this switch or even deactivate the driver's side
air bag. What do I do?
</P>
<P>
   A: It would be difficult to find a dealership willing to do this
for your car. Dealerships shy away from this kind of work due to
the liability involved in it. To have this work done, try going to
an after-market air-conditioning repair shop, or a stereo
installation specialist. The best solution, though, would be to
contact Ford Motor Co. and see what they recommend. Their toll-free
customer service number is 1-800-392-3673. Q: How do the Serbs and
the Albanians identify each other as enemies? They look exactly
alike to me. Is it a language difference? But then how could they
kill each other at a distance?
</P>
<P>
   A: To understand how ethnic Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo
province could identify one another when they appear to look so
much alike, you much first understand they exist in two nearly
separate societies. The schools, churches, businesses and
neighborhoods _ even whole villages _ were separate.
</P>
<P>
   Serbs are Orthodox Christian; Albanians are Muslim. So even if
an ethnic Albanian looked like a Serb, you could likely tell he was
Albanian because of the neighborhood he lived, stores he shopped
at, church he attended, or where his children went to school.
</P>
<P>
   Basically, the physical differences _ even posture, walk,
mannerisms, dress, etc. _ between ethnic Serbs and ethnic Albanians
in Kosovo is not really stark enough for anyone to recognize. This
helps explain why many of the recent atrocities were up-close and
personal. Kosovar Serbs and Albanians identify one another most
easily through their language, which is very different. For
example, they have entirely different names for each city, town and
village in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   This ``separate society'' way of living in the province helps
explain why it was so easy for Serb troops and police to target
ethnic Albanians en masse during the NATO bombing campaign. You
could go to a whole town and wipe out hundreds of Albanians at
once, never concerned about killing a Serb, or vice-versa. Or if
you saw a convoy of people on a road during the bombing campaign,
you could be quite certain they were Albanian.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Were the Atlanta Hawks ever members of the ABA before they
came to Atlanta? Which league, if any, were they a part of before
joining the NBA? A friend of mine and I have been arguing about
this and would love an answer to settle the score.
</P>
<P>
   A: Hopefully, this will provide the olive branch of peace,
depending on who is on which side of the fight. The Atlanta Hawks
had never been in the American Basketball Association. The
basketball team was founded in 1945 as the Buffalo Bisons, a member
of the National Basketball League. Then they changed cities and
played as the Tri-Cities Blackhawks in 1946, while still remaining
in the NBL.
</P>
<P>
   By the time the Hawks franchise had become the Milwaukee Hawks,
in 1951, they had joined the NBA _ and there they remained. After
Milwaukee, they moved to St. Louis in 1955, eventually coming to
roost in Atlanta in 1968.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Just out of curiosity, what does the Libertarian Party stand
for? What is its party platform?
</P>
<P>
   A: In the words of Bill Winter, Libertarian Party director of
communications, ``The party platform calls for vigorous defense of
the Bill of Rights, free enterprise, civil liberties, free trade,
no meddling overseas, and private charity.'' For more information,
you may write to the party headquarters: 2600 Virginia Ave. NW,
Suite 100, Washington DC 20037.
</P>
<P>
   Q: We heard an official say firefighters always carry portable
hydrants. Now, what in the world is a portable hydrant?
</P>
<P>
   A: Portable hydrants are an appliance that essentially lets
other hoses be hooked up to a hose that has water in it. Mainly,
this lets other ``appliances,'' such as other fire hoses or deluge
guns, known to the layman as water cannons, take and distribute the
water from a supply hose rather than have each appliance hooked up
individually to a fire hydrant.
</P>
<P>
   You must have a water supply _ whether it's a tank truck, creek,
pond or a fire hydrant _ to fill your firefighting hoses. Then,
with a portable hydrant, you can drop one hose in the pond (or hook
it up to a distant hydrant) and feed several other hoses or
appliances off that one.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I get a schedule for Turner Classic Movies?
</P>
<P>
   A: If you're online, this address _
http://TCM.turner.com/CALENDAR/month/ _ will give you the current
month's programs. Or to order the Now Playing Guide, call
1-800-826-1002 or write: Now Playing, P.O. Box 420934, Palm Coast,
FL 32142-0934. The cost for the guide, issued monthly, is $9.97 for
one year, $19.94 for two years.
</P>
<P>
   Q: It was reported recently that Coca-Cola at one time was ``the
second-most valuable company in America.'' What company is
currently the most valuable?
</P>
<P>
   A: It's Microsoft. It had a market value (as of the end of June)
of $452.97 billion. The second-most valuable company was General
Electric, with a market value of $358.88 billion. Although
Coca-Cola has slipped, don't shed too many tears. Its market value
was $152.68 billion.
</P>
<P>
   Market values and rankings obviously are subject to fluctuation
as stock prices change, but with Microsoft so far ahead of all the
other companies, even General Electric, its top ranking isn't
likely to change soon.
</P>
<P>
   Q: A recent article about Elton John left me with a question:
Wasn't he engaged or married at one point?
</P>
<P>
   A: Yes, the singer was married for a short time, as has been
widely reported. After an engagement of five days, John was wed to
German sound engineer Renate Blauel on Feb. 14, 1984, in Australia.
John and his bride had met in mid-1982 at London's AIR Studio while
John was dubbing vocals for his 1983 album, ``Too Low for Zero,''
and later, on Montserrat, the two reportedly had discussed the
possibility of marriage.
</P>
<P>
   There were no children born to John and Blauel. The pair often
lived continents apart for months at a time, and on Nov. 18, 1988,
their no-fault divorce was announced. Blauel said she and John were
parting amicably ``and genuinely intend to remain the best of
friends.'' After the divorce, she withdrew to the 17th century
cottage in England she received in the settlement, along with a sum
reported to be as high as $45 million.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I read that information about the new Gemini North telescope
can be found on the Internet, but no URL was listed. Do you know
what it is?
</P>
<P>
   A: For information about Gemini Observatory, try this site _
www.noao.edu/usgp _ which is operated by the National Optical
Astronomy Observatories.
</P>
<P>
   Q: When and where will the Libertarian Party nominating national
convention be held, and who can I contact to attend?
</P>
<P>
   A: The convention will be June 30-July 3, 2000, in Anaheim,
Calif. Delegates who will vote to select the presidential candidate
must be selected by the 50 state affiliate parties, said spokesman
Bill Winter at the party's Washington headquarters. A lot of the
convention, however, is open to the public, such as some business
sessions, some speeches, and some political workshops. And there's
a ``good chance'' that C-SPAN will televise most or all of the
convention, Winter added. You can call 202-333-0008, extension 228,
to be put on a mailing list for updates.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Who is Mia Hamm, and why is such a fuss being made about her?
</P>
<P>
   A: Soccer superstar Hamm is the celebrated 27-year-old forward
on the U.S. national team playing for the World Cup. She has been
very much in the news of late _ ranking, in fact, at the top of a
Sports Business Daily survey on ``most marketable female
athletes,'' ahead of Michelle Kwan, Venus Williams and Tara
Lipinski.
</P>
<P>
   Some of Hamm's accomplishments are her membership on the 1996
Olympic gold medal and 1991 World Cup championship teams, all-time
record of 109 international goals, four championships at the
University of North Carolina, endorsements for Nike, appearances in
Gatorade and Pert shampoo commercials. She even was dubbed by
People magazine as one of its ``50 Most Beautiful People.''
</P>
<P>
   END
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
