<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 11:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1633 &Cx1f; tad-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NEWS-QUESTIONS08-COX     07-07 1524
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NEWS-QUESTIONS08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Q &AMP; A ON THE NEWS
 &HT;    By Colin Bessonette
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Have a question about the news? Colin Bessonette will try to get
an answer. Call 404-222-2002, or write him at The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, Ga. 30302, or e-mail
him at q&AMP;(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Q: Can you tell me how to get in touch with former Sen. Bill
Bradley's presidential campaign?
</P>
<P>
   A: The Democrat's official website _ www.billbradley.com _
offers many options for campaign contributions, plus information on
Bradley and some of his speeches. To get in touch with the campaign
the old-fashioned way, write Bill Bradley for President, Inc., 396
Pleasant Valley Way, West Orange, N.J. 07052. Or call the campaign
headquarters toll-free at 1-888-643-9799.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have a Government Approval form to have the air bag on-off
switch installed in my Ford. I have yet to find a Ford dealership
that will install this switch or even deactivate the driver's side
air bag. What do I do?
</P>
<P>
   A: It would be difficult to find a dealership willing to do this
for your car. Dealerships shy away from this kind of work due to
the liability involved in it. To have this work done, try going to
an after-market air-conditioning repair shop, or a stereo
installation specialist. The best solution, though, would be to
contact Ford Motor Co. and see what they recommend. Their toll-free
customer service number is 1-800-392-3673. Q: How do the Serbs and
the Albanians identify each other as enemies? They look exactly
alike to me. Is it a language difference? But then how could they
kill each other at a distance?
</P>
<P>
   A: To understand how ethnic Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo
province could identify one another when they appear to look so
much alike, you much first understand they exist in two nearly
separate societies. The schools, churches, businesses and
neighborhoods _ even whole villages _ were separate.
</P>
<P>
   Serbs are Orthodox Christian; Albanians are Muslim. So even if
an ethnic Albanian looked like a Serb, you could likely tell he was
Albanian because of the neighborhood he lived, stores he shopped
at, church he attended, or where his children went to school.
</P>
<P>
   Basically, the physical differences _ even posture, walk,
mannerisms, dress, etc. _ between ethnic Serbs and ethnic Albanians
in Kosovo is not really stark enough for anyone to recognize. This
helps explain why many of the recent atrocities were up-close and
personal. Kosovar Serbs and Albanians identify one another most
easily through their language, which is very different. For
example, they have entirely different names for each city, town and
village in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   This ``separate society'' way of living in the province helps
explain why it was so easy for Serb troops and police to target
ethnic Albanians en masse during the NATO bombing campaign. You
could go to a whole town and wipe out hundreds of Albanians at
once, never concerned about killing a Serb, or vice-versa. Or if
you saw a convoy of people on a road during the bombing campaign,
you could be quite certain they were Albanian.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Were the Atlanta Hawks ever members of the ABA before they
came to Atlanta? Which league, if any, were they a part of before
joining the NBA? A friend of mine and I have been arguing about
this and would love an answer to settle the score.
</P>
<P>
   A: Hopefully, this will provide the olive branch of peace,
depending on who is on which side of the fight. The Atlanta Hawks
had never been in the American Basketball Association. The
basketball team was founded in 1945 as the Buffalo Bisons, a member
of the National Basketball League. Then they changed cities and
played as the Tri-Cities Blackhawks in 1946, while still remaining
in the NBL.
</P>
<P>
   By the time the Hawks franchise had become the Milwaukee Hawks,
in 1951, they had joined the NBA _ and there they remained. After
Milwaukee, they moved to St. Louis in 1955, eventually coming to
roost in Atlanta in 1968.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Just out of curiosity, what does the Libertarian Party stand
for? What is its party platform?
</P>
<P>
   A: In the words of Bill Winter, Libertarian Party director of
communications, ``The party platform calls for vigorous defense of
the Bill of Rights, free enterprise, civil liberties, free trade,
no meddling overseas, and private charity.'' For more information,
you may write to the party headquarters: 2600 Virginia Ave. NW,
Suite 100, Washington DC 20037.
</P>
<P>
   Q: We heard an official say firefighters always carry portable
