 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  
Magazine shows how to limit computer crashes 
By Charles Haddad  
c.1999 Cox News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ It's a sad fact of everyday life with a computer that
these machines still crash a lot. Learn how you can limit crashes
for Macintosh computers in the July issue of MacAddict. The
magazine also instructs how to recover from those really nasty
crashes that can wipe out your data.
</P>
<P>
   The same issue of MacAddict takes a look at how you can use your
Mac to create audio CDs from old vinyl records. It's a complicated
process, but the story walks you through the technique step by
step.
</P>
<P>
   On CD-ROM
</P>
<P>
   Movie wasn't enough? Now you can explore ``StarWars: The Phantom
Menace'' in-depth on computer CD. LucasArts has released a new
program about the movie called ``Episode 1: Insider's Guide.'' It
includes interviews with director George Lucas and his production
team about the making of the movie. Also included is the complete
screenplay, with annotations and 2,000 images from the making of
the ``Phantom Menace.'' This CD is available only for PCs running
Windows 95 or higher.
</P>
<P>
   Activision has released a sequel to its popular role-playing war
game ``Heavy Gear.'' In the sequel, the once-warring robot soldiers
of planet Terra Novan unite to battle a new enemy. You command an
elite planetary strike force to hit the invaders behind their
lines. This game, like its predecessor, features graphic violence.
</P>
<P>
   Online
</P>
<P>
   Here's a fun place for kids to learn about health and science.
It's called BrainPop, and it features miniature movies, streamed
through the Web, about various science topics. The topics range
from vision to diabetes to water. The site was developed by Dr.
Avraham Kadar, who has been a medical staff fellow in the immunity
section of the National Institute of Allergies and Infectious
Diseases. You'll find BrainPop at www.brainpop.com
</P>
<P>
   /indexgen.asp
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
