 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  
DJX Keyboard makes music fun 
By James Cummings  
c.1999 Cox News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Yamaha DJX portable keyboard offers some of the
features of professional electronic keyboards at a price that makes
it accessible to younger customers, according to Yamaha Corp. of
America.
</P>
<P>
   The keyboard is focused on dance styles and has automatic
accompaniment capabilities for music ranging from ``Rap'' to
``Techno'' to ``Rave.'' It also offers sounds such as sampled drum
loops and human voices.
</P>
<P>
   The DJX, like most portable keyboards for the amateur market, is
designed so that even a novice can make music immediately.
</P>
<P>
   The suggested retail price for the DJX keyboard is $459.95,
which is significantly cheaper than professional model keyboards
with the same types of accompaniments and sound styles, according
to Yamaha.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Yamaha DJX could well be the Nintendo of the music
industry,'' said Yamaha marketing executive Jim Presley.
</P>
<P>
   A spokesman for the Ace Music Superstore in Dayton said the
store carries the DJX but they sell out quickly whenever a shipment
comes in.
</P>
<P>
   You can get additional information about the keyboard at the
Yamaha Web site at www.yamaha.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
