   &UR; NEW YORK  &LR; (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   NY-BLACKOUT (New York) _ Developments in the blackout that
affected a crowded Manhattan neighborhood, with 200,000 people
still without power.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   NY-MRSCLINTON (Dateline to kum, N.Y.) _ Hillary Clinton on the
hustings in her New York senatorial bid. By Adam Nagourney.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL &LR;  (``f'' code)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-KATZENBERG (Los Angeles) _ Walt Disney and Jeffrey
Katzenberg have settled a bitter lawsuit filed by the former studio
chief claiming he was owed at least $250 million. Terms of the
settlement were not disclosed. By Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 11 a.m., stocks were little changed: The
Dow Jones industrial average was down about 5 points, the S&AMP;P 500
was up 3 points, the Nasdaq composite index was up 8 points. The
30-year bond was yielding 6.07 percent. Crude oil was at $19.74 a
barrel, gold at $258.2 a troy ounce. European markets were slightly
lower, with London down 0.5 percent and Frankfurt down 0.43
percent. The Nikkei closed down 0.51 percent and the Hang Seng down
0.8 percent. By Robert D. Hershey.
</P>
<P>
   YAHOO-EARNINGS (Undated) _ Yahoo is expected to report
second-quarter earnings after the markets close. The consensus
forecast is 8 cents a share. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-GE (Undated) _ Boeing chooses General Electric to supply
engines for its new longer-range 777X jetliner over Pratt &AMP; Whitney
and Rolls-Royce. Unlike past engine orders, this contract, valued
at $25 billion over 20 years, is exclusive. By Laurence Zuckerman.
</P>
<P>
   SINGAPORE-MALAYSIA (Singapore) _ A look at an increasingly
bitter fight between Singapore and Malaysia over the status of
over-the-counter Malaysian stocks traded in Singapore. Malaysia
outlawed such trading last September when it imposed harsh controls
to keep capital in the country. That left 172,000 investors holding
nearly $4 billion in these stocks, which they couldn't sell. By
Wayne Arnold.
</P>
<P>
   TOYOTA-SENIORITY (Tokyo) _ Toyota Motor is negotiating with its
union to eliminate seniority as a major factor in determining the
salaries of its white collar workers. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   AIR-CANADA-LABOR (Toronto) _ Some 5,000 flight attendants at Air
Canada International are set to strike at midnight as contract
negotiations make little progress. By Timothy Pritchard.
</P>
<P>
   MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The daily Marketplace column.
</P>
<P>
   ECONSCENE (Undated) _ The weekly Economic Scene column. By
Michael M. Weinstein.
