</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MINIS08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini views
 &HT;    By Eleanor Ringel Gillespie, Bob Longino and Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Hilary and Jackie'' (R) _ Never quite hitting its intended
crescendo, this real-life psychological drama about the
relationship between two musical sisters still strikes some major
chords. Emily Watson (``Breaking the Waves'') stars as Jacqueline
du Pre, a world-famous cellist who died in 1987 of multiple
sclerosis. Rachel Griffiths plays her sister, Hilary, who swapped a
career for cozy domesticity. The mystical finale makes up for a lot
of the unfilled-in blanks that come before it. (VHS
</P>
<P>
   priced for rental; available on DVD, $24.95.) Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   _Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The King and I'' (G) _ Richard Rich (``The Swan Princess'')
has taken a brush and made ``The King and I,'' the first animated
feature based on a work by Rodgers and Hammerstein. But does this
second-rate animated King of Siam really need to high-five the paw
of his pet black leopard? This king's now got a hot-air balloon to
fly around in and swoops into action when somebody's about to
drown. Kids will probably be charmed. For everybody else, it's a
puzzlement. Grade: D+
</P>
<P>
   _Bob Longino
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Wing Commander'' (PG-13) _ It's one loopy space lark with
Freddie Prinze Jr. and ``Scream's'' wonderfully woozy killer
Matthew Lillard playing fighter pilots in a galaxy at war. Earth is
threatened by a lumbering band of catlike creatures wrapped in
armadillo armor. It takes eons for ``Wing,'' based on the popular
computer game, to get to the first big dogfight. Grade: D+
</P>
<P>
   _Bob Longino
</P>
