<P>
   TOURDEFRANCE (Blois, France) _ To all those who have been asking
that question, Mario Cipollini gave his answer Wednesday: In his
usual place, crossing the finish line ahead of everybody else in
the Tour de France. For the fourth consecutive day, a stage ended
in a mass sprint and, for the first time, Cipollini, who is
regarded, especially by himself, as the fastest sprinter around,
proved it. By Samuel Abt.
</P>
