immigrants were predominantly nonprofessionals.
 &HT;    Vilpesh Patel's father, Jayantibhai, was one of those who had to
migrate against his will. He used to be a prosperous dry-goods
merchant in Lira, a town in central Uganda. In 1972, when
Jayantibhai was 32, Idi Amin ordered the confiscation of all Asian
property, stripping the owners of their Ugandan nationality.
 &HT;    After a few months in a refugee camp in Austria, where he was
separated from his wife and young children, Jayantibhai Patel ended
