   STRESS-REBELLION (Undated) _ There's a quiet rebellion going on
in households throughout the country, led by busy people who simply
refuse to let today's high-tech communications devices beep and
flash their way into the quiet of their homes. By Patricia Wen.
1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-BROWN (San Francicso) _ Mayor Willie Brown, seeking
reelection, is getting a lesson in the perils of the politics of
prosperity. By Lynda Gorov. 1060 words.
</P>
<P>
   ELECTRONIC-GIVING (Undated) _ In at least 2,000 churches across
the country the faithful are having money automatically transferred
from their accounts to their church's account. By Sara Neufeld.
1275 words. PHOTO
