nation's biggest tobacco companies in the first class-action case
to reach a verdict, holding that they are guilty of conspiring to
hide the danger and addictiveness of cigarettes. The six-person
jury in a Miami state court also said that both compensatory and
punitive damages could be awarded, throwing open the door to
hundreds of thousands of potential claims by current and former
smokers in Florida. By Barry Meier. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET
in ``a'' news file.)
