<P>
   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HILLARY-CLINTON (Pindars Corners, N.Y.) _ Hillary Rodham
Clinton, embarking on an unprecedented campaign for the U.S.
Senate, vows to try again to overhaul the nation's troubled
health-care system. The first lady used the debut of her own
political career to address the carpetbagger issue of why she was
seeking election in New York state even though she has never lived
there. By STEWART M. POWELL. (Also filed in the ``a'' category.
Albany Times Union photos available on the Wieck database.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-2000 (Salt Lake City) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush appears
here with officials from seven Western states in the home of a
possible rival for the Republican presidential nomination, Sen.
Orrin Hatch. Bush, who also plans campaign stops in Portland, Ore.,
and Seattle, names members of an information technology council,
headed by Michael Dell of Dell Computer. By JULIE MASON.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BORDER-CONGESTION (Laredo, Texas) _ Stepped-up searches for
drugs and undocumented immigrants have resulted in congested
highways and bridges on the U.S.-Mexico border, posing a challenge
for the increase in trade between the two nations, a government
report says. By DANE SCHILLER. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SECURITIES-PROBE (San Antonio) _ A Mexico City man has filed a
lawsuit against the San Antonio investment firm InverWorld
Securities, alleging mismanagement of an account valued at more
than $1 million. The firm that caters to wealthy Mexicans also is
being scrutinized by federal and state regulators. By JOHN
MacCORMACK. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PGA-TOUR (Undated) _ David Duval already has set a
single-season earnings record and won four tournaments. But Tiger
Woods, with three victories in his last four tournaments, is the
talk of the PGA Tour as it hits the halfway point of the season.
And still to come in 1999 are the British Open, the PGA
Championship and the Ryder Cup. By EDDIE SEFKO.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ALLSTARS-HOUSTON (Phoenix, Ariz.) _ Houston Astros' first
baseman Jeff Bagwell and pitchers Jose Lima, Mike Hampton and Billy
Wagner are chosen for the National League All-Star team. By CARLTON
THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   With: BBN-LOPEZ-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS-ROOKIE (Phoenix, Ariz.) _ Rookie Wade Miller will
make his major-league debut for the Houston Astros tonight as they
take on the Arizona Diamondbacks. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ With only 18 months left in his
eight-year presidency, Bill Clinton refuses to accept lame-duck
status. He is racing around the nation as though he were just
beginning his tenure rather than limping toward the end of it.
Since much of his moral leadership has been squandered, he wants to
improve his legacy by the time he leaves office _ if he can. By
ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Already filed.)
</P>
