move the concrete, pour it, level it, then smooth and rough it.
Weather is an important consideration. Since all the work will be
done outdoors, you must pick a dry day with no rain in the
forecast. The temperature should be between 65 and 75 degrees
Fahrenheit. (Edward R. Lipinski/New York Times Illustration) LITE
