in the town, 25 miles north of Pristina. The gendarmes were trying
to escort the women into the Serb-held side of a bridge which has
become a de facto border between the Serb and ethnic Albanian
sectors of the city. The women were unable to reach their
destination due to the unrest. (Alan Chin/New York Times Photo)
